The aim of this post is to provide a whistle-stop tour of the latest version of SvelteKit. We're going to build a developer portfolio and blog website, that fetches data from your RSS feed, as well as the GitHub API.

articles.description:
Just an update, for SvelteKit 1.0.0 and later...

The environment module includes the browser property, which returns true if being run client-side.

For example,

import { browser } from '$app/environment';

if (browser) {
  // Running client-side
  // Can use the browser APIs here
} else {
  // Running server-side
  // Can use private env vars here
}
